<subSubSection id="6EDC654FFE42FF89FF0AFB6E5EB3FA4D" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" type="description">
<paragraph id="267936C4FE42FF89FF0AFB6E5FFAFB4D" blockId="2.[166,1225,1183,1530]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Widespread in Europe Scotland, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FCF2FB515FCEFB0E" box="[803,904,1183,1209]" name="United Kingdom" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">England</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FC42FB515FBEFB0E" box="[915,1016,1183,1209]" name="Belgium" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Belgium</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FBD2FB515820FB0E" box="[1027,1126,1183,1209]" name="Netherlands" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Holland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FBA3FB6E5883FB0D" box="[1138,1221,1184,1210]" name="France" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">France</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FF77FB715D46FB6E" box="[166,256,1215,1241]" name="Austria" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Austria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FEC0FB715DC4FB6E" box="[273,386,1215,1241]" name="Germany" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Germany</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FE42FB715E66FB6E" box="[403,544,1215,1241]" name="Switzerland" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FDE1FB715E32FB6E" box="[560,628,1215,1241]" name="Spain" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Spain</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FD54FB715EFAFB6E" box="[645,700,1215,1241]" name="Italy" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Italy</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FD1CFB715FCBFB6E" box="[717,909,1215,1241]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FC4CFB71584CFB6E" box="[925,1034,1215,1241]" name="Romania" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Romania</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FBCAFB715836FB6E" box="[1051,1136,1215,1241]" name="Greece" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Greece</collectingCountry>
. North Africa: 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FF2CFB2E5D2DFB4D" box="[253,363,1248,1274]" name="Morocco" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Morocco</collectingCountry>
. Middle East: 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FDDEFB115E20FB4E" box="[527,614,1247,1273]" name="Turkey" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Turkey</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FDA0FB2E5EE3FB4D" box="[625,677,1248,1274]" name="Iraq" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Iraq</collectingCountry>
. 
<collectingCountry id="5ED17654FE42FF89FD7EFB2E5EA2FB4D" box="[687,740,1248,1274]" name="Iran" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Iran</collectingCountry>
: 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE42FF89FD3FFB115FFEFB4D" author="Rozkosny, R." box="[750,952,1247,1274]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" pagination="1 - 100" refId="ref6810" refString="Rozkosny, R. 1987. A review of the Palaearctic Sciomyzidae (Diptera). Biologia 86. Prirodovedecka Fakulta, Univerzita J. E. Purkyne, Brne, 1 - 100." type="book chapter" year="1987">Rozkošný (1987)</bibRefCitation>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="267936C4FE42FF89FF0AFACE5EB3FA4D" blockId="2.[166,1225,1183,1530]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">
B i o l o g y. I m m a t u r e s t a g e s: 
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE42FF89FD9CFB315F49FAAD" author="Vala, J. - C. &amp; Caillet, C. &amp; Gasc, C." box="[589,783,1279,1306]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" pagination="1675 - 1680" refId="ref7654" refString="Vala, J. - C., Caillet, C., Gasc, C. 1987. Biology and immature stages of Dichetophora obliterata, a snail killing fly (Diptera - Sciomyzidae). Canadian Journal of Zoology, 65, 1675 - 1680." type="journal article" year="1987">Vala et al. (1987)</bibRefCitation>
described and figured in details all the immature stages, provided information on the biology, and the life cycle. Eggs were often laid (after a long pre-oviposition period up to 2 months) on the shells of living terrestrial snails (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE42FF89FF26FA915DF1FACD" author="Vala, J. - C. &amp; Caillet, C. &amp; Gasc, C." box="[247,439,1375,1402]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" pagination="1675 - 1680" refId="ref7654" refString="Vala, J. - C., Caillet, C., Gasc, C. 1987. Biology and immature stages of Dichetophora obliterata, a snail killing fly (Diptera - Sciomyzidae). Canadian Journal of Zoology, 65, 1675 - 1680." type="journal article" year="1987">Vala et al., 1987</bibRefCitation>
). In the laboratory, the first-instar larvae fed as internal parasitoids on 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE42FF89FF1AFA4E5DE2FA2E" baseAuthorityName="Da Costa" baseAuthorityYear="1778" box="[203,420,1407,1433]" class="Gastropoda" family="Lauriidae" genus="Lauria" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="cylindracea">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE42FF89FF1AFA4E5DE2FA2E" box="[203,420,1407,1433]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Lauria cylindracea</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and later instars fed on more large size 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE42FF89FCA1FAB15F93FA2E" authorityName="A. Ferussac" authorityYear="1821" box="[880,981,1407,1433]" class="Gastropoda" family="Geomitridae" genus="Helicella" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE42FF89FCA1FAB15F93FA2E" box="[880,981,1407,1433]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Helicella</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="E1C64D47FE42FF89FBDCFAB158C5FA2D" box="[1037,1155,1407,1434]" class="Gastropoda" family="Helicidae" genus="Theba" kingdom="Animalia" order="Stylommatophora" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" phylum="Mollusca" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="14B2EAD6FE42FF89FBDCFAB15812FA2E" box="[1037,1108,1407,1433]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="23">Theba</emphasis>
spp
</taxonomicName>
(
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE42FF89FB40FAB15D69FA0D" author="Vala, J. - C. &amp; Caillet, C. &amp; Gasc, C." pageId="2" pageNumber="23" pagination="1675 - 1680" refId="ref7654" refString="Vala, J. - C., Caillet, C., Gasc, C. 1987. Biology and immature stages of Dichetophora obliterata, a snail killing fly (Diptera - Sciomyzidae). Canadian Journal of Zoology, 65, 1675 - 1680." type="journal article" year="1987">Vala et al., 1987</bibRefCitation>
). Overwintering occurs as the mature larva, then the puparium (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE42FF89FB94FA515CA5FA6D" author="Vala, J. - C. &amp; Caillet, C. &amp; Gasc, C." pageId="2" pageNumber="23" pagination="1675 - 1680" refId="ref7654" refString="Vala, J. - C., Caillet, C., Gasc, C. 1987. Biology and immature stages of Dichetophora obliterata, a snail killing fly (Diptera - Sciomyzidae). Canadian Journal of Zoology, 65, 1675 - 1680." type="journal article" year="1987">Vala et al., 1987</bibRefCitation>
). Pupariation occurs either in the shell of the host snail or away from it (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE42FF89FB98FA715CA5FA4D" author="Vala, J. - C. &amp; Caillet, C. &amp; Gasc, C." pageId="2" pageNumber="23" pagination="1675 - 1680" refId="ref7654" refString="Vala, J. - C., Caillet, C., Gasc, C. 1987. Biology and immature stages of Dichetophora obliterata, a snail killing fly (Diptera - Sciomyzidae). Canadian Journal of Zoology, 65, 1675 - 1680." type="journal article" year="1987">Vala et al., 1987</bibRefCitation>
). This species is univoltine (
<bibRefCitation id="42574B35FE42FF89FDF9FA115EAEFA4D" author="Vala, J. - C. &amp; Caillet, C. &amp; Gasc, C." box="[552,744,1503,1530]" pageId="2" pageNumber="23" pagination="1675 - 1680" refId="ref7654" refString="Vala, J. - C., Caillet, C., Gasc, C. 1987. Biology and immature stages of Dichetophora obliterata, a snail killing fly (Diptera - Sciomyzidae). Canadian Journal of Zoology, 65, 1675 - 1680." type="journal article" year="1987">Vala et al., 1987</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
